\end_layout

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $X(t)$
\end_inset

 be a Gaussian random field and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(t)=\mathbb{E}[X(t)]=0$
\end_inset

.
 Consider the mean-zero process 
\begin_inset Formula $X(t)-\mu(t)$
\end_inset

.
 We are interested in expressing the sample paths 
\begin_inset Formula $X(t,\omega)-\mu(t)$
\end_inset

 as a series in an orthonormal basis 
